\f0 \cf4 /tmp
\f2 \cf2  space is a problem regardless of what kind of filesystem lies under\
it, but in a configuration where 
\f0 \cf4 /tmp
\f2 \cf2  is not a separate file system it will essentially have\
the whole disk available, as the default installation only creates a single 
\f0 \cf4 /
\f2 \cf2  partition. On\
the other hand, a RAM-based 
\f0 \cf4 /tmp
\f2 \cf2  (as with 
\f0 \cf4 tmpfs
\f2 \cf2 ) will almost certainly be much\
smaller, which can lead to applications filling up the filesystem much more easily.\
