\f2\b0 Since the 
\f0 \cf4 /dev/shm
\f2 \cf2  directory is intended to be world-writable, there is a risk of resource\
exhaustion if it is not bound to a separate partition.\

\f0 \cf4 /dev/shm
\f2 \cf2  utilizing 
\f0 \cf4 tmpfs
\f2 \cf2  can be resized using the 
\f0 \cf4 size=\{size\}
\f2 \cf2  parameter in the\
