\f1\b Description:\

\f2\b0 The RPM Package Manager implements GPG key signing to verify package integrity\
during and after installation.\

\f1\b Rationale:\

\f2\b0 It is important to ensure that updates are obtained from a valid source to protect against\
spoofing that could lead to the inadvertent installation of malware on the system. To this\
end, verify that GPG keys are configured correctly for your system.
\fs20\fsmilli10080 Page 128\

\f0 Internal Only - General\

\f1\b\fs24 Audit:\
List all GPG key URLs\

\f2\b0 Each repository should have a 
\f0 \cf4 gpgkey
\f2 \cf2  with a URL pointing to the location of the GPG\
key, either local or remote.\

\f4\fs20\fsmilli10080 # grep -r gpgkey /etc/yum.repos.d/* /etc/dnf/dnf.conf\

\f1\b\fs24 List installed GPG keys\

\f2\b0 Run the following script to list the currently installed keys. These are the active keys\
used for verification and installation of RPMs. The packages are fake, they are\
generated on the fly by 
\f0 \cf4 dnf
\f2 \cf2  or 
\f0 \cf4 rpm
\f2 \cf2  during the import of keys from the URL specified in\
the repository configuration.\

\f3\i Example:\

\f4\i0\fs20\fsmilli10080 # for RPM_PACKAGE in $(rpm -q gpg-pubkey); do\
echo "RPM: $\{RPM_PACKAGE\}"\
RPM_SUMMARY=$(rpm -q --queryformat "%\{SUMMARY\}" "$\{RPM_PACKAGE\}")\
RPM_PACKAGER=$(rpm -q --queryformat "%\{PACKAGER\}" "$\{RPM_PACKAGE\}")\
RPM_DATE=$(date +%Y-%m-%d -d "1970-1-1+$((0x$(rpm -q --queryformat\
"%\{RELEASE\}" "$\{RPM_PACKAGE\}") ))sec")\
RPM_KEY_ID=$(rpm -q --queryformat "%\{VERSION\}" "$\{RPM_PACKAGE\}")\
echo "Packager: $\{RPM_PACKAGER\}\
Summary: $\{RPM_SUMMARY\}\
Creation date: $\{RPM_DATE\}\
Key ID: $\{RPM_KEY_ID\}\
"\
done\

