\f1\i0\b\fs24 \cf2 Profile Applicability:\

\f0\b0 \'95
\f2  Level 1 - Server\

\f0 \'95
\f2  Level 1 - Workstation\

\f1\b Description:\

\f2\b0 The 
\f0 \cf4 gpgcheck
\f2 \cf2  option controls verifying package signatures after download. This option\
is configurable as a global option in the main section of 
\f0 \cf4 /etc/dnf/dnf.conf
\f2 \cf2  and a per\
repository option in individual files in the 
\f0 \cf4 /etc/yum.repos.d/*
\f2 \cf2  directory.\
The option is enabled if 
\f0 \cf4 gpgcheck
\f2 \cf2  is set to 
\f0 \cf4 1
\f2 \cf2 , 
\f0 \cf4 true
\f2 \cf2 , or 
\f0 \cf4 yes
\f2 \cf2 . The option is disabled if\

\f0 \cf4 gpgcheck
\f2 \cf2  is set to 
\f0 \cf4 0
\f2 \cf2 , 
\f0 \cf4 false
\f2 \cf2 , or 
\f0 \cf4 no
\f2 \cf2 . If an invalid option is set, e.g. 
\f0 \cf4 gpgcheck=2
\f2 \cf2 , the\
global option will be used.\
Settings in files in the 
\f0 \cf4 /etc/yum.repos.d/
\f2 \cf2  directory take precedence over the global\
configuration.\

\f1\b Rationale:\

\f2\b0 It is important to ensure that an RPM's package signature is always checked prior to\
installation to ensure that the software is obtained from a trusted source.\

\f1\b Audit:\

\f2\b0 Run the following command and verify that global configuration for 
\f0 \cf4 gpgcheck
\f2 \cf2  is\
enabled:\

\f4\fs20\fsmilli10080 # grep -Pi --\
'^\\h*gpgcheck\\h*=\\h*(1|true|yes)\\b' /etc/dnf/dnf.conf\

\f2\fs24 Verify the output is: 
\f0 \cf4 gpgcheck=1
\f2 \cf2 , 
\f0 \cf4 gpgcheck=true
\f2 \cf2 , or 
\f0 \cf4 gpgcheck=yes
\f2 \cf2 .\

\f3\i Example output:\

\f4\i0\fs20\fsmilli10080 gpgcheck=1\

\f2\fs24 Run the following command to verify 
\f0 \cf4 gpgcheck
\f2 \cf2  is not disabled in a file in the\

\f0 \cf4 /etc/yum.repos.d/
\f2 \cf2  directory:\

\f4\fs20\fsmilli10080 # grep -Pris --\
'^\\h*gpgcheck\\h*=\\h*(0|[2-9]|[1-9][0-9]+|false|no)\\b'\
/etc/yum.repos.d/\

\f2\fs24 Nothing should be returned
\fs20\fsmilli10080 Page 132\

\f0 Internal Only - General\

\f1\b\fs24 Remediation:\

\f2\b0 Edit 
\f0 \cf4 /etc/dnf/dnf.conf
\f2 \cf2  and set 
\f0 \cf4 gpgcheck=1
\f2 \cf2  in the 
\f0 \cf4 [main]
\f2 \cf2  section.\

\f3\i Example\

\f4\i0\fs20\fsmilli10080 [main]\
gpgcheck=1\

\f2\fs24 Edit any failing files in 
\f0 \cf4 /etc/yum.repos.d/*
\f2 \cf2  and set all instances starting with\

\f0 \cf4 gpgcheck
\f2 \cf2  to 
\f0 \cf4 1
\f2 \cf2 .\

\f3\i Example:\

\f4\i0\fs20\fsmilli10080 # find /etc/yum.repos.d/ -name "*.repo" -exec echo "Checking:" \{\} \\; -exec\
sed -i 's/^gpgcheck\\s*=\\s*.*/gpgcheck=1/' \{\} \\;\

\f1\b\fs24 Default Value:\

\f2\b0 gpgcheck=1\

