\f3\i\fs32\fsmilli16080 \cf3 1.2.1.5 Ensure weak dependencies are configured (Automated)\

\f1\i0\b\fs24 \cf2 Profile Applicability:\

\f0\b0 \'95
\f2  Level 2 - Server\

\f0 \'95
\f2  Level 2 - Workstation\

\f1\b Description:\

\f2\b0 The RPM packaging specification allows for 3 levels of dependencies to be declared:\

\f0\fs20\fsmilli10080 \'95
\f2  
\fs24 hard dependencies (
\f0 \cf4 Requires
\f2 \cf2  / 
\f0 \cf4 Provides
\f2 \cf2 ) for packages which must be installed\
for a minimal installation of the application to function\

\f0\fs20\fsmilli10080 \'95
\f2  
\fs24 weak dependencies (
\f0 \cf4 Recommends
\f2 \cf2  / 
\f0 \cf4 Supplements
\f2 \cf2 ) for packages which provide\
additional features, but which are not required for a minimal installation to\
function\

\f0\fs20\fsmilli10080 \'95
\f2  
\fs24 hints (
\f0 \cf4 Suggests
\f2 \cf2  / 
\f0 \cf4 Enhances
\f2 \cf2 ) for packages which offer add-ons which might be\
useful.\

\f1\b Rationale:\

\f2\b0 Unless a system specifically requires the additional capabilities provides by the weak\
dependencies, it is recommended that the packages are not installed to reduce the\
potential attack surface.\

\f1\b Audit:\

\f2\b0 Run the following command and verify that global configuration for 
\f0 \cf4 install_weak_deps\

\f2 \cf2 is disabled:\

\f4\fs20\fsmilli10080 # grep -Pi --\
'^\\h*install_weak_deps\\h*=\\h*(0|false|no)\\b' /etc/dnf/dnf.conf\

\f2\fs24 Verify the output one of the following: 
\f0 \cf4 install_weak_deps=0
\f2 \cf2 ,\

\f0 \cf4 install_weak_deps=false
\f2 \cf2 , or 
\f0 \cf4 install_weak_deps=no
\f2 \cf2 .\

\f3\i Example output:\

\f4\i0\fs20\fsmilli10080 install_weak_deps=0\

\f1\b\fs24 Note
\f2\b0 : If no output is returned, this should be considered a failure as the default value is\
enabled.
\fs20\fsmilli10080 Page 138\

\f0 Internal Only - General\

\f1\b\fs24 Remediation:\

\f2\b0 Edit 
\f0 \cf4 /etc/dnf/dnf.conf
\f2 \cf2  and set 
\f0 \cf4 install_weak_deps=0
\f2 \cf2  in the 
\f0 \cf4 [main]
\f2 \cf2  section.\

\f4\fs20\fsmilli10080 [main]\
install_weak_deps=0\

\f3\i\fs24 Example script:\

\f4\i0\fs20\fsmilli10080 #!/usr/bin/env bash\
\{\
if grep -Pq '^install_weak_deps' /etc/dnf/dnf.conf; then\
sed -i 's/^install_weak_deps\\s*=\\s*.*/install_weak_deps=0/'\
/etc/dnf/dnf.conf\
else\
