\f3\i\fs32\fsmilli16080 \cf3 1.3.1.2 Ensure SELinux is not disabled in bootloader configuration\
(Automated)\

\f1\i0\b\fs24 \cf2 Profile Applicability:\

\f0\b0 \'95
\f2  Level 1 - Server\

\f0 \'95
\f2  Level 1 - Workstation\

\f1\b Description:\

\f2\b0 Configure SELINUX to be enabled at boot time and verify that it has not been\
overwritten by the grub boot parameters.\

\f1\b Rationale:\

\f2\b0 SELinux must be enabled at boot time in your grub configuration to ensure that the\
controls it provides are not overridden.\

\f1\b Impact:\

\f2\b0 Files created while SELinux is disabled are not labeled at all. This behavior causes\
problems when changing to enforcing mode because files are labeled incorrectly or are\
not labeled at all. To prevent incorrectly labeled and unlabeled files from causing\
problems, file systems are automatically relabeled when changing from the disabled\
state to permissive or enforcing mode. This can be a long running process that should\
be accounted for as it may extend downtime during initial re-boot.\

\f1\b Audit:\

\f2\b0 Run the following command to verify that neither the 
\f0 \cf4 selinux=0
\f2 \cf2  or 
\f0 \cf4 enforcing=0\

\f2 \cf2 parameters have been set:\

\f4\fs20\fsmilli10080 # grubby --info=ALL | grep -Po '(selinux|enforcing)=0\\b'\

\f2\fs24 Nothing should be returned\
Run the following command to verify the 
\f0 \cf4 selinux=0
\f2 \cf2  and 
\f0 \cf4 enforcing=0
\f2 \cf2  parameters\
were not configured by the deprecated 
\f0 \cf4 grub2-mkconfig
\f2 \cf2  command:\

\f4\fs20\fsmilli10080 # grep -Prs --\
'^\\h*([^#\\n\\r]+\\h+)?kernelopts=([^#\\n\\r]+\\h+)?(selinux|enforcing)=0\\b'\
/boot/grub2 /boot/efi\

\f2\fs24 Nothing should be returned
\fs20\fsmilli10080 Page 147\

\f0 Internal Only - General\

\f1\b\fs24 Remediation:\

\f2\b0 Run the following command to remove the 
\f0 \cf4 selinux=0
\f2 \cf2  and 
\f0 \cf4 enforcing=0
\f2 \cf2  parameters:\

\f4\fs20\fsmilli10080 grubby --update-kernel ALL --remove-args "selinux=0 enforcing=0"\

\f2\fs24 Run the following command to remove the 
\f0 \cf4 selinux=0
\f2 \cf2  and 
\f0 \cf4 enforcing=0
\f2 \cf2  parameters if\
they were created by the deprecated 
\f0 \cf4 grub2-mkconfig
