\f2\b0 Restricting the use of 
\f0 \cf4 su
\f2 \cf2  , and using 
\f0 \cf4 sudo
\f2 \cf2  in its place, provides system administrators\
better control of the escalation of user privileges to execute privileged commands. The\
sudo utility also provides a better logging and audit mechanism, as it can log each\
command executed via 
\f0 \cf4 sudo
\f2 \cf2  , whereas 
\f0 \cf4 su
\f2 \cf2  can only record that a user executed the 
\f0 \cf4 su\

\f2 \cf2 program.\

