\f0\fs20\fsmilli10080 \'95
\f2  
\f0\fs24 \cf4 /etc/authselect/custom
\f2 \cf2  - Place for administrator-defined profiles.\
Profile Files - Each profile consists of one or more of these files which provide a\
mandatory profile description and describe the changes that are done to the system:\

\f0\fs20\fsmilli10080 \'95
\f2  
\f0\fs24 \cf4 README
\f2 \cf2  - Description of the profile. The first line must be a name of the profile.\

\f0\fs20\fsmilli10080 \'95
\f2  
\f0\fs24 \cf4 system-auth
\f2 \cf2  - PAM stack that is included from nearly all individual service\
configuration files.\

\f0\fs20\fsmilli10080 \'95
\f2  
\f0\fs24 \cf4 password-auth
\f2 \cf2 , 
\f0 \cf4 smartcard-auth
\f2 \cf2 , 
\f0 \cf4 fingerprint-auth
\f2 \cf2  - These PAM stacks are\
for applications which handle authentication from different types of devices via\
