function, an attacker could still break the system if they got access to the 
\f0 \cf4 /etc/passwd\

\f2 \cf2 file. This can be mitigated by using shadowed passwords, thus moving the passwords in\
the 
\f0 \cf4 /etc/passwd
\f2 \cf2  file to 
\f0 \cf4 /etc/shadow
\f2 \cf2 . The 
\f0 \cf4 /etc/shadow
\f2 \cf2  file is set so only root will be\
